8:
Everyone's busy with their own
problems.
But you know what?
13:
I can't take it anymore! I can't just sit
around doing nothing!
18:
I... I've got to HUNT!
Together, alongside all of you!
23:
Without further ado...
I present to you Mia the Treasure
Santa!
27:
Let's get to huntin' so we can find
gifts for everyone in Shibuya!
31:
Check you out, Mia! That outfit's
SUPER cute on you!
35:
Isn't it?! Lilie hooked me up with it!
Apparently it's from the Guild!
40:
So you're... a tiger Santa treasure
hunter. Kind of a mouthful, don't you
think?
44:
Hehe, that's why Lilie and I decided
to shorten it to "Treasure Santa!"
47:
I always give out gifts to the children
in Palpebra for the holiday festival,
but this year I want to give some to
the Shibuyan children, too!
51:
Which is why... I've become Santa!
My plan is to scour the Kaleidoscope
for treasures that I can give out as
gifts!
55:
Uh, if gifts are all you're after, there
are easier ways to get them than
venturing into the Kaleidoscope...
59:
Sho, Sho, Sho. You don't get it, do
you?
63:
I REALLY want to go on a huntâ€”with
you and Nao, that is!
67:
Seriously? THAT'S your whole
reason? I mean, hey, at least you're
honest about it...
71:
That's as good a reason as any! As a
member of the Crimson Blades, I'm
not about to go and ignore the call
of treasure!
76:
That's the spirit! There's been a lot of
shifts lately, and I hear off-world
artifacts are popping up! We're
bound to find riches!
80:
All right, enough standing around!
To the Kaleidoscope! To TREASURE!
Let's GO!
90:
No artifacts, no elemental gems,
NOTHING! Where's all the treasure?!
94:
Hmm, it is pretty barren in here.
Maybe someone else already
picked the place clean?
99:
Well we can't leave empty-handed!
My reputation as a Treasure Santa is
on the line! We've gotta find
SOMETHING!
105:
That sounds like a YOU problem,
honestlyâ€”
122:
Whoa!
That thing is HUGE! What is it?!
128:
A... a kraken?! Pretty sure that's not
supposed to be in the Kaleidoscope!
136:
Yeah, we should probably get the
hell out of here.
141:
No! We can't retreat before we've
found any treasure!
146:
Don't worry, treasure hunter
extraordinaire Mia will protect you
both!
157:
Wh-whoa! You've gotta be kidding
me! Hold on, Mia!
166:
*huff* *huff* Y-yeah...
Action like this is part of the thrill of
the hunt!
172:
Yeah, well, that "thrill" of yours just
about gave me a heart attack! At
least the damn squid is gone... We
shouldâ€”
183:
Phew, we made it to safety...
But what do we do now?
188:
Ugh, I'm gonna be sick... But it DOES
kinda feel like a waste to leave
empty-handed after coming this far.
193:
Wait!
My Treasure Santa senses are
tingling!
198: There! There's treasure, I can feel it!
202:
Hmm, what are these things? Some
kind of small machines?
206:
Mia, those... are game consoles!
From my world!
211:
Ooh, games! I played some of those
in Qualia City! They're those flashy
things that go BEEP BEEP BOOP when
you touch them, right?
216:
Uh, really old ones, maybe. But
whatever, close enough. Let's see,
this one's portable... Oh, and this
one's a home console!
219:
Sweet, check this one outâ€”it's the
latest model! If we bring these back
with us, we might be able to get
them working!
223:
Then we'll be able to play games
back home?! Oooh, I wanna play, I
wanna play! Lemme hear those
beautiful beeps and boops!
228:
Look there! That's a manga Yumu
and his friends used to read! Oh,
and this one is my favorite!
232:
We've hit the mother lode of
Shibuyan treasures!
235:
Awesome! Great job, fellow Treasure
Santas! Now we can spread some
serious cheer!
240:
Hey, I just came along to help, I
never agreed to be a "Treasure
Santa"! But, whatever, you can't go
wrong giving out presents.
245:
This whole adventure was so
exciting! Treasure hunting is so
much fun!
249:
ISN'T IT?!
I'm glad I was able to give you the
gift of a successful huntâ€”
253: Wait, that's it! I've got it!
259:
Happy Holidays, everyone!
Santa Mia has arrived!
263:
But I'm not just going to stand
around here and hand out present
to you allâ€”that wouldn't be any fun,
would it?
266:
Instead, to make things more
interesting, I've hidden gifts all
around Shibuya! I've even drawn up
a map with hints for you!
270:
The treasure hunt begins... NOW! Go
get your gifts!
273:
What's with that furball? Why would
she make us do something so
boring?
276:
Whoever finds the first prize slip will
get... All these game consoles! And
second prize gets all of these
mangas!
279:
Well, it's not like I have anything else
to do. Guess I'll join in.
283:
Man, everyone seems pretty
pumped about this huntâ€”Mia most
of all, heh.
287:
Nothing brings people together
more than some good
old-fashioned fun. You love to see it.
293:
Haha! How about joining the hunt
yourself, Seiji?
298:
Yeah! I saw how your eyes lit up
when we told you about the game
consoles and manga, Mr. Takamori!
301:
Man, I can't find ANYTHING!
Hey, Santa Mia! Give me a hint!
304:
All right, if you insist! I'll lend you a
helping paw, hehe.
308: Treasure Santa Mia joins the hunt!
